gomodel:SYNGO_4991  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 4: Neo1 binds in trans to Cbln4/Nrxn1α-SS4+ complexes, forming bona fide adhesion complexes.\n\nFigure 2: Cbln4 deletion in the EC selectively blocks LTP at EC→DG synapses. (EC = entorhinal cortex, DG = dentate gyrus).\n\nFigure 5: Postsynaptic deletion of Neo1 in the DG severely impaired LTP in EC→DG synapses of both MPP (Fig. 5 E-G) and LPP connections (Fig. 5 H-J), similar to the presynaptic deletion of Cbln4 in the EC (Fig. 1).\n\nTaken together, authors concluded that Cbln4 connects presynaptic Neurexins with postsynaptic neogenin-1 (Neo1) into a transsynaptic complex (with Neo1 in the PSD membrane, Fig. 6).. Experimental description: Supplementary M&M: \"All mouse experiments were performed in accordance with protocols approved by the Administrative Panel on Laboratory Animal Care (APLAC) at Stanford University. Cbln4 and Neo1 conditional KO (cKO) mice were previously described (PMID: 27143755, PMID: 28714144). Neo1 cKO mice have LoxP sites flanking the exon 1 of Neo1 gene. Wild type CD-1 mice were obtained from Charles River Laboratories.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4991" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

